PROJECT COVENANT — ON THE USE OF AI

This software is free for everyone to use, fork, and build on. But it carries
one promise to the Hacker News community that every fork and contribution is
asked, in good faith, to keep:

  AI is opt-in. It runs only if a user supplies their own API key and chooses
  to. With no key, the extension makes no AI calls of any kind.

  AI is for reading, never for speaking. The AI features exist solely to help a
  person read — summarizing threads and matching stories to their stated
  interests. This software MUST NOT be updated to use AI to generate, draft,
  suggest, or post comments, replies, or submissions, or to vote, on the user's
  behalf or anyone else's.

Automating participation with AI would erode the signal that makes Hacker News
worth reading. Please honor this covenant. It is the spirit in which the
project is shared.
